  "text": "In this study a detailedsubtyping of T cell populations present in diseased and healthy nasal mucosa was conducted by means of flow cytometry. Most T cells in the nasal mucosa were CD45RA negative and of an effector phenotype, which is in agreement with earlier data [CITATION_1] and in opposite with the T cells circulating in the bloodthatpreferentially carry markers of the naïve T cell phenotype.",
